                <h3 class="subheading">Introduction</h3>
                @* <p>@Html.Raw(@Model.BlogSummary.Replace("\n", "<br>"))</p> *@
                <p>
                    Tata Motors is back in the spotlight with the unveiling of the much-anticipated <span class="font-weight-700">Altroz Facelift 2025</span>, a stylish upgrade to its premium hatchback offering. Launched at a starting price of <span class="font-weight-700">₹6.89 lakh (ex-showroom)</span>, the updated Altroz brings sharper aesthetics, smarter technology, and improved safety—setting a new benchmark in the competitive Indian hatchback segment. With rivals like the Hyundai i20 and Maruti Baleno constantly raising the bar, this facelift positions the Altroz as a serious contender. But what exactly has changed? Let’s take a detailed look at what’s new in the 2025 Tata Altroz.
                </p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/june/tataaltrozfacelift2025/2025-tata-altroz-facelift.jpg" alt="tataaltrozfacelift2025" title="tataaltrozfacelift2025" /></div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Design and Exterior Updates</h3>
                <p>The <span class="font-weight-700">2025 Altroz facelift</span> has been thoroughly refreshed on the outside, giving it a more mature and premium appearance while retaining its sporty hatchback proportions. </p>
                <h3 class="subheading">LED Projector Headlamps with DRLs</h3>
                <p>Tata has equipped the Altroz with <span class="font-weight-700">sleek LED projector headlamps</span> paired with <span class="font-weight-700">eyebrow-style daytime running lights</span>, creating a bold and aggressive front profile. </p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/june/tataaltrozfacelift2025/ledheadlampsanddrls.png" alt="ledheadlampsanddrls" title="ledheadlampsanddrls" /></div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Flush-Type Door Handles</h3>
                <p>A segment-first addition, the Altroz now features <span class="font-weight-700">flush door handles</span>—similar to those seen on the Nexon EV and Tata Curvv concepts. These not only elevate the car's styling but also improve aerodynamics. </p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/june/tataaltrozfacelift2025/flushdoorhandles.png" alt="flushdoorhandles" title="flushdoorhandles" /></div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Connected LED Tail Lamps</h3>
                <p>At the rear, the <span class="font-weight-700">new connected LED tail lamps</span> add a sense of width and modernity, tying together the rear fascia beautifully. </p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/june/tataaltrozfacelift2025/newtaillamp.jpg" alt="newtaillamp" title="newtaillamp" /></div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="subheading">New Alloy Wheels</h3>
                <p>The facelifted Altroz rolls on <span class="font-weight-700">freshly designed alloy wheels</span>, enhancing its stance and sporty appeal across variants. </p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/june/tataaltrozfacelift2025/alloywheels.jpg" alt="alloywheels" title="alloywheels" /></div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="subheading">New Color Options</h3>
                <p>Although not officially confirmed, Tata is likely to introduce <span class="font-weight-700">new exterior shades</span> to keep the lineup vibrant and youthful. </p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Interior and Cabin Enhancements</h3>
                <p>Step inside, and the updates become even more impressive. Tata has modernized the cabin to meet evolving customer expectations.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Dual 10.25-inch Displays</h3>
                <p>One of the biggest upgrades comes in the form of <span class="font-weight-700">dual 10.25-inch displays</span>—a touchscreen infotainment system and a fully digital instrument cluster. This setup is intuitive, crisp, and a major leap forward in cabin tech. </p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/june/tataaltrozfacelift2025/altrozinfotaiment.jpg" alt="altrozinfotaiment" title="altrozinfotaiment" /></div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Two-Spoke Steering Wheel</h3>
                <p>Inspired by the new Nexon and the upcoming Curvv SUV, the facelift features a <span class="font-weight-700">two-spoke steering wheel with an illuminated Tata logo</span>, adding a luxurious flair to the driving experience. </p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/june/tataaltrozfacelift2025/altrozsteering.jpg" alt="altrozsteering" title="altrozsteering" /></div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Ventilated Front Seats</h3>
                <p>Upper trims now offer <span class="font-weight-700">ventilated front seats</span>, a much-appreciated feature in Indian summers—boosting comfort during long drives.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Voice-Activated Sunroof</h3>
                <p>The Altroz facelift includes a <span class="font-weight-700">single-pane electric sunroof</span> that supports <span class="font-weight-700">voice commands</span>, bringing both convenience and a touch of flair to the drive. </p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/june/tataaltrozfacelift2025/sunroof.jpg" alt="sunroof" title="sunroof" /></div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Features and Technology Additions </h3>
                <p>Tata hasn’t held back when it comes to packing the Altroz facelift with premium, segment-leading features. </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">360-Degree Camera:</span> Assists in low-speed maneuvering and tight parking spaces.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">6 Airbags Standard on Higher Trims:</span> Improved occupant protection across variants.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Electronic Stability Control (ESC):</span> Ensures better grip and control during sudden direction changes. </li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">ISOFIX Child Seat Anchors:</span> Standard in higher variants, offering secure child seat integration. </li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Wireless Android Auto & Apple CarPlay:</span> Combined with OTA updates for seamless connectivity.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>These features make the Altroz not just smarter, but also a much safer and more user-friendly hatchback. </p>
                 <h3 class="subheading">Engine Options and Performance</h3>
                <p>Under the hood, Tata offers a wide range of powertrain choices to meet every driving preference, from fuel efficiency to turbocharged fun. </p>
                <h3 class="subheading">1.2L Naturally Aspirated Petrol </h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Power:</span> 88 PS </li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Transmission:</span> 5-speed Manual or 6-speed DCT</li>
                    <li>Ideal for urban users looking for low-cost, hassle-free ownership. </li>
                </ul>
                <h3 class="subheading">1.2L Turbocharged Petrol</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Power:</span> 120 PS </li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Transmission:</span> 6-speed Manual</li>
                    <li>Appeals to performance enthusiasts who want more from their hatchback. </li>
                </ul>
                <h3 class="subheading">1.5L Diesel</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Power:</span> 90 PS</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Transmission:</span> 5-speed Manual </li>
                    <li>One of the few diesel options still available in this segment.</li>
                </ul>
                <h3 class="subheading">1.2L CNG</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Power:</span> 73.5 PS</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Transmission:</span> 5-speed Manual </li>
                    <li>A great pick for fuel-conscious users, especially in metro cities. </li>
                </ul>
                <p>With four distinct engine choices, the Altroz offers unparalleled flexibility in its class. </p>
